                <head>143. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_ZA1">Zoli</persName> and Foreign Minister
                        <persName corresp="#p_PG1">Pella</persName> met with President <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> during the <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss> Heads of Government Meeting in Paris. According to the
                    memorandum of conversation of the meeting, which took place on December 17, the
                    President spoke of the need for European integration, with the Italians stating
                    that they too supported such a policy. The leaders also discussed the Italian
                    economy and reviewed the events of the <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>
                    meeting. For text of the memorandum of conversation, see volume IV, pages
                    242–244.</p>
            </div>
